name: Percipio Business Advisors
description:
Providing accounting and finance solutions to meet the needs of privately held businesses, non-profit organizations, and individuals.

Rest easy, we will handle your Accounting, Mergers & Acquisitions, and Tax services so that you can focus on what you do best, running your business.

company_updates.description: Happy Labor Day from your friends here at Percipio Business Advisors! Today we celebrate the dedication and hard work of individuals and teams across all industries. Thank you to all workers across the country!

In honor of National Intern Day, we wanted to take a moment to introduce our Summer 2025 Consulting Interns Emma Dengler and Mia Dougherty! Since joining Percipio Business Advisors in May, they’ve been contributing to client success through weekly accounting work, month-end close tasks, and hands-on collaboration with our team.
 
We have loved watching them learn and grow in their roles this summer and can't wait to see all they do!
 
Happy National Intern Day!
 
 #PercipioBusinessAdvisors #ConsultingInterns #NationalInternDay

Please join us in welcoming Trevor Koger, CPA to the Percipio Business Advisors team as a Consulting Manager!

Trevor works with businesses to help streamline processes and navigate complex technical accounting transactions. With his prior experience working in public accounting, he brings valuable knowledge on audit across a wide range of industries. 

Welcome, Trevor!

Nick works with businesses to outsource their accounting and finance needs. His prior management accounting experience provides him with the ability to identify the unique needs of businesses and works to provide effective and transparent reporting.

Hello from all of us at Percipio Business Advisors! 
 
It’s been a little while since we’ve checked in with our LinkedIn community — so here’s a quick look at what we’ve been up to in 2025!
 
We’ve been keeping busy not just in the office, but out in the community and having a great time together as a team:
 
April – We kicked things off with a fun night at Topgolf! Lots of friendly competition, plenty of laughs, and let’s just say… some swings were more stylish than effective. We also joined forces with our friends at HD for a park cleanup to help give back to our local parks.
 
May – Members of the PBA team spent time volunteering with Habitat for Humanity of Omaha, gaining hands-on experience in homebuilding while supporting a great cause. It was both humbling and inspiring. Our golfers also teed off at the Griffin Golf Classic in support of Gretna East High School Booster Clubs.
 
June – We proudly sponsored and participated in the Bike With Mike mental health fundraiser. A fun and rainy day of biking, connecting, and of course, celebrating with some well-earned tacos! Our team hit the greens again for a great cause at the Goodwill Golf Tournament, proudly participating as event sponsors and enjoying a day of golf in support of Goodwill’s impactful programs.
 
July – Summer fun continues with our sand volleyball league! This week we celebrated our first win of the season!
 
We’re proud of the work we do every day, but even more proud of the team we’ve built and the ways we support our community together.
 
#PercipioBusinessAdvisors #CommunityMatters #TeamCulture #GivingBack #HabitatForHumanity #BikeWithMike #GriffinGolfClassic #SandVolleyball #LifeAtPBA

Bryce manages clients’ day-to-day financial operations and provides comprehensive outsourced accounting solutions. Prior to joining Percipio, Bryce worked in the mortgage industry as a residential lender out of Sioux Falls, SD.

Welcome, Bryce!

We are so excited to announce Morgan Schreiner has joined the Percipio Business Advisors team as a Business Operations Specialist! 

Morgan has been working on applying process improvements, implementing internal software and other systems that support client services. Her prior experience includes R&D innovation spanning product & packaging development, process improvement and entrepreneurial acquisition integration.
